Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide fries 
(peeling optional). Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with 
@oil{to taste}, season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then 
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

Halve the @cabbage{1}, cut out and discard the tough core, then thinly slice. 
Add the cabbage to a #bowl{} along with half the @aioli{2%sachet for whole recipe} 
and mix to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.

== Chicken Strips ==

Beat @egg{1}(for 2p) in a separate bowl. In another bowl, season the 
@breadcrumbs{1%pack} with salt and pepper.

Lay the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%g} out on a cutting board. Slice the chicken 
into 2cm strips. Season with salt and pepper. Dip the chicken strips first into 
the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring they're completely coated. Transfer 
to a clean #plate{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw 
chicken and its packaging. Discard excess egg.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

When the potatoes have 10 mins of cooking time left, place a large pan over 
high heat with enough oil to coat the bottom. Once hot, carefully lay the 
chicken strips into the pan. Fry until golden brown on the outside, 
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust heat if necessary. Once golden, remove the 
chicken from the pan. Discard the oil remaining in the pan.

> TIP: Allow the oil to get hot before adding the chicken so it can fry properly.

== Loaded Fries ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, add them to an #oven dish{}. Top with chicken, 
@chorizo{100%g}(sliced) and a scattering of @grated cheese{50%g}.

Return to the top shelf of the oven until the cheese is melted and chicken is 
cooked through, another ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no 
longer pink in the middle.

== Gochujang Aioli ==

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix the @gochujang paste{2%sachet}, @honey{1%sachet} 
and remaining aioli. Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}.

== To Serve ==

Carefully remove the loaded fries from the oven and scatter over the sliced 
scallion. Drizzle the gochujang aioli over the top. Allow everyone to help 
themselves at the table. Serve with cabbage slaw alongside.